value.value: 子育て行動異常
altered behavior of animals that affects the ability of offspring to survive
摂食／飲水行動異常
altered ability or inability to eat or drink, or unusual choice or avoidance of foods or drink
発毛異常
any anomaly in the amount of hair or abnormal onset of hair growth cycle or development, or abnormal hair pattern
毛質異常
irregular or unusual appearance of the structure of the hair
外皮／毛の色素沈着異常
irregular or unusual pigmentation of the hair
グルコース恒常性異常
anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of glucose in the fluids and tissues
インスリン血中濃度上昇
greater than normal levels of insulin in blood
出生前死亡率
death anytime between fertilization and birth (Mus: approximately E18.5)

definition.value: Note that the name of this term has previously been embryonic lethality. In many species, the terms prenatal lethality and embryonic lethality are used interchangeably. However, this is not technically correct and we have modified this ontology to define the prenatal period to include the embryonic stages distinctly from the fetal stages. The names embryonic lethality and embryonic death have been retained as a narrow synonyms to aid in searching for those species that may use these terms as synonyms.

value.value: 出生時死亡率
death anytime within the perinatal period (Mus: E18.5 through postnatal day 1)
出生後死亡率
premature death anytime between the neonatal period and weaning age (Mus: P1 to approximately 3 weeks of age)
成熟前死
death after weaning age, but before the normal life span (Mus: after 3 weeks of age)
発育パターン異常
abnormal systematic arrangement of the developing body along an axis
胚組織形態異常
any structural anomaly of the embryonic tissue part of the whole embryo
胚外組織形態異常
any structural anomaly of the membranes involved with embryonic protection and nutrition
胚成長／体重／体長異常
limited or accelerated growth or development apparent during the embryonic period (sensu Mus: up to E14, or the completion of organogenesis)
出生後成長／体重／体長異常
increased or decreased average body size, weight or growth characteristic abnormalities manifesting after birth
視覚異常
any anomaly in the ability to see
眼形態異常
any structural anomaly of the spheroid organ and optic nerve that serves to detect light
皮膚色素沈着異常
anomaly in the coloration of the skin due to changes in the amount, shape, or distribution of cells producing pigment
感覚毛の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the stiff hairs projecting from the face around the nose of most mammals which act as touch receptors
歯形態異常
any anomaly in the size, shape or structure of the hard or soft tissues of the skeletal element within the mouth that is composed of dentine and used to procure or masticate food
耳形態異常
any structural anomaly of any of the structures involved in the ear or vestibular system
筋肉生理異常
any functional anomaly of the muscle, not due to an anatomical defect
筋肉形態異常
any structural anomaly of the contractile tissue that produces movement in animals
四肢形態異常
any structural anomaly of the projecting paired appendages of an animal trunk, used in particular for movement and grasping; usually denotes the arm and/or legs in mammalian species
指形態異常
any structural anomaly of the fingers or toes
尾部形態異常
any structural anomaly of the flexible elongated appendage located at the caudal end of the torso in many species; it is usually continuous with the vertebral column
骨格発達異常
any anomaly in the formation of bone tissue
軸骨格形態異常
any structural anomaly of the articulated bones of the cranium and vertebral column
四肢骨格形態異常
any structural anomaly of the limb or autopod bones
頭蓋顔面骨形態異常
any structural anomaly of the cranial or facial bones
脂質恒常性異常
anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of lipids in the fluids and tissues
高度口渇
excessive desire to drink, or to drink unusual fluids
造血異常

abnormal development of blood cells in the fetal and adult organism; in the fetus cells develop in the aorta, genital ridge and mesonephros region and later in the liver; in adults cells normally develop in the bone marrow and lymphatic tissues
心臓血管系形態異常
any structural anomaly of the heart or vascular tissue
血液循環異常
failure or atypical movement in the flow of blood from the heart to the vasculature and back to the heart
呼吸器系形態異常
any structural anomaly of pulmonary tissues
呼吸器系生理異常
any functional anomaly of the pulmonary system; inability or reduced ability to intake and exchange oxygen and carbon dioxide with the environment
腎臓形態異常
any structural anomaly of either of the two excretory organs that filter wastes (especially urea) from the blood and excrete them and water in urine
腎生理異常
any functional anomaly and/or activity of either of the two excretory organs that filter wastes (especially urea) from the blood and excrete them and water in urine
肝臓／胆汁系形態異常
any structural anomaly of any of the tissues of the liver or biliary system
肝臓／胆汁系生理異常
any functional anomaly of the tissues of the liver or biliary system
B細胞分化異常
atypical production of or inability to produce mature B cells, and/or accumulation of B cell precursors
T細胞分化異常
atypical production of or inability to produce mature T cells, and/or accumulation of T cell precursors
過敏症
immune response that results in tissue injury
神経管形態／発達異常
any structural anomaly of the hollow epithelial tube found on the dorsal side of the vertebrate embryo that develops into the central nervous system (i.e. brain and spinal cord)
脳形態異常

any structural anomaly of the brain, one of the two components of the central nervous system and the center of thought and emotion; controls coordination, bodily activities and the interpretation of information from the senses (sight, hearing, smell, etc.)
生殖系形態異常
structural or developmental anomaly of any of the tissues involved in the reproductive system
受精率／繁殖力異常
anomaly in the reproductive capability of an organism or population to produce live offspring
腺形態異常
any structural anomaly of an organ that functions as a secretory or excretory organ
